# XUnity.AiTranslator — Project Overview

## Purpose

A Flutter desktop application that acts as a **local LLM translation endpoint** for [XUnity.AutoTranslator](https://github.com/bbepis/XUnity.AutoTranslator) (a Unity game auto-translation plugin). It runs an embedded HTTP server (default port 8080) that XUnity connects to via its `CustomTranslate` endpoint. The app provides a GUI to configure LLM providers, prompt templates, concurrency, and output filtering.

XUnity config:
```ini
[Custom]
Url=http://127.0.0.1:8080/translate
```

## Architecture

Three logical layers:

1. **HTTP layer** — `shelf`-based server exposing `GET/POST /translate`, `GET /health`, `GET /info`
2. **Translation layer** — concurrency-controlled orchestrator that acquires slots, calls the LLM, and records logs
3. **LLM client layer** — OpenAI-compatible chat completions client with model listing and caching

State is managed with **Riverpod**; config is persisted via **shared_preferences**.

## Directory Layout

```
lib/
  main.dart                              # Entry point; 3-tab side-nav (Config / Server / Logs)
  models/translation_config.dart         # Core models: TranslationConfig, LLMProviderConfig, ProviderDefinitions
  providers/app_providers.dart           # All Riverpod providers (config, server state, logs, locale)
  services/
    http_server.dart                     # shelf HTTP server
    enhanced_translation_service.dart    # Slot-based concurrency + translation orchestration
    llm_service.dart                     # LLM API client (OpenAI-compatible)
    locale_service.dart                  # UI language persistence
  widgets/
    config_panel.dart                    # Full settings GUI
    server_control_panel.dart            # Start/stop + status
    translation_logs.dart                # Real-time log viewer
    language_switcher.dart               # EN/ZH toggle
  theme/app_theme.dart                   # Dark theme constants and spacing tokens
  l10n/                                  # EN + ZH ARB localization files
go/                                      # go-flutter (hover) alternative desktop embedding
linux/ windows/                          # Standard Flutter native runners
```

## Key Design Decisions

- **Multiple providers**: OpenAI, DeepSeek, OpenRouter, Google AI Studio, and custom — each with its own API key, base URL, model, and sampling params. Active provider is switched at runtime.
- **Hot config reload**: Only a port change restarts the HTTP server; all other config (prompt, model, concurrency) is applied live via `EnhancedTranslationService.updateConfig`.
- **Slot-based concurrency**: Configurable limit (default 3) on simultaneous in-flight LLM requests.
- **Localization**: UI supports EN and ZH via Flutter's `flutter_localizations` + `intl`.
